  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Systemic antibiotics >2 days treatment, starting on encounter of diagnosis",
    "At least 2 primary care/medical home visits between ages 20-40 years (inclusive) for adult controls",
    "Positive pathology report requiring 1 CUI from inflammation group (Group 1) AND 1 or more from any other groups (Groups 2-6)",
    "Absence of incidental appendectomy procedures",
    "Exclusion of comorbid conditions in same encounter for cases without pathology reports"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "The appendicitis phenotype algorithm identifies three case types: Case 1 uses pathology reports with SNOMED-CT concept unique identifiers (CUIs) requiring inflammation markers plus other pathological features; Case 2 identifies patients without pathology reports but with systemic antibiotic treatment (>2 days) or interventional radiology procedures, excluding those with specific comorbidities; Case 3 identifies patients with reported history of appendicitis/appendectomy excluding incidental procedures. Controls are patients without appendicitis diagnosis or history, excluding those with appendicitis-related ICD-9 codes. Adult controls additionally require 2+ primary care visits between ages 20-40. The algorithm uses ICD-9 diagnosis codes (540.XX), CPT procedure codes for interventional radiology, medication lists for systemic antibiotics, and extensive SNOMED-CT pathology concepts organized into 6 groups (inflammation, ulcer, hyperemia, necrosis, fibrosis, and other findings).",
